 

This project is part of my internship with *Prodigy Infotech, under **Task 3 â€“ Password Strength Checker. The application checks the strength of user-entered passwords and categorizes them as **Weak, **Moderate, or **Strong* based on specific criteria.

---

## âœ… Features

- Checks for *minimum password length*
- Ensures the presence of:
  - Uppercase letters
  - Lowercase letters
  - Digits
  - Special characters
- Outputs strength level:
  - Weak
  - Moderate
  - Strong

---

## ðŸ’» Technologies Used

- Java
- Scanner for user input
- Regex (optional for pattern checks)
- String and Character class operations

---

## ðŸ§  Logic Used

```java
if (password.length() < 8) {
    System.out.println("Weak Password");
} else {
    boolean hasUpper = false, hasLower = false, hasDigit = false, hasSpecial = false;
    for (char ch : password.toCharArray()) {
        if (Character.isUpperCase(ch)) hasUpper = true;
        else if (Character.isLowerCase(ch)) hasLower = true;
        else if (Character.isDigit(ch)) hasDigit = true;
        else hasSpecial = true;
    }

    if (hasUpper && hasLower && hasDigit && hasSpecial) {
        System.out.println("Strong Password");
    } else {
        System.out.println("Moderate Password");
    }
}
